snippets.snippet: Local favorite and all-organic cookie company Bang Cookies has now opened its SECOND location in Jersey City  this one downtown at 128 Newark Avenue.
snippets.title: Bang Cookies' Second Jersey City Storefront is Now Open ...

snippets.snippet: Bang Cookies will soon open at 128 Newark Avenue. (In the space that was formerly home to Dolya Cafe). Bang Cookies is a locally owned bakery that made its debut years ago at the Grove street farmers market. Owner George Kuan had been working on his cookie recipe for over 12 years before launching Bang Cookies.
snippets.title: Bang Cookies Opening its Second Jersey City Shop Soon ...

snippets.snippet: Bang Cookies to replace Dolya Cafe. Bang Cookies is expanding their retail presence in Jersey City. Word is the gourmet cookie startup is planning to open a new retail location downtown along the Newark Avenue Pedestrian Plaza.
snippets.title: Bang Cookies Opening Downtown Jersey City Location ...

snippets.snippet: Bang Cookies started on the farmers market circuit about three years ago and quickly outgrew its original shop in Hackensack  a trip to the Newark Farmers Market with 50 cookies that sold out in minutes was just the beginning of the success that put Bang Cookies on the map.
